description: For sale: $329,000. If you are looking for a home in the country on over 6 acres that feels like a farmhouse yet is equipped with today's modern look and conveniences - this is it! A wonderfully unique home that has been renovated to the studs - new sheet rock, wiring, floating hardwood, tile, and carpeting throughout. In keeping with the rustic charm the original wood ceiling was left exposed while adding steel beams for extra support, wrapped in cedar for a beautiful finished look. Kitchen features quartz counter tops, stainless steel appliances (including a beverage fridge), island with seating, subway tile back splash, coffee station area, and tons of natural light filtering through the bay window. There is a master suite on each level, do your own thing with the spacious walk-in closets which lead into the full baths.  Each of the 4 bedrooms have access to their own bathroom - super convenient! Added extras: washer/dryer hook-ups on each level, maintenance-free steel roof, vinyl siding, central air, & a large deck with a gazebo - perfect for those spring/summer nights!  There is a 3-car garage, red horse barn & shed, pole building connected to a dated barn, and a playhouse which all can be used for storage or made back into a hobby farm! The quality craftsmanship throughout along with the versatility of the land make this a property you won't want to slip away!

description: For sale: $340,000. If you have horses or want horses, this home is for you! This 4-bedroom 3-bath country home built in 1983 in Carlton. The large, bright kitchen has a new dishwasher and  nice roomy dining area with a new window. The property is on 10 wooded acres and has a 6-stall pole barn with water and electricity and extra room for hay and toys. An automatic watering station outside your barn to keep your horses hydrated. There is an outdoor riding arena and a motocross track which is also great for riding your bikes or horses on through the oak scenery. A new metal roof was just installed on the house as well as a new sliding glass door, some new carpet, and some fresh paint. The home features a sunny family room on the main floor and a spacious family room in the basement with 3/4 bath off of it and large storage room. Part of the 10 acres is enclosed by electric fence and the house is surrounded by a wooden fence. You are located minutes from the Black Bear Casino or Carlton and about 30 minutes from Duluth.

description: For sale: $389,900. This home has everything you need to simplify and relax,  built in 2012 this space is ready for you to enjoy the peace and quiet of northern Minnesota all season long.   Privacy abounds at this Hay Lake retreat, contemporary building materials with this 5 bedroom,  east and west wing bedrooms off the main open concept living make it easy and comfortable to entertain guests and family.  Vaulted ceilings and a stone fireplace are the focal point of the great room with double sliding glass doors to the lake.   The master bedroom has a soaking tub and large windows overlooking the lake and hardwood forest in the backyard, giving you a relaxing place to soak away to the sounds and sights of nature.   Very energy efficient layout with in floor heating system and efficient on demand boiler system, mini split to help with heating and cooling and a central wood burning fireplace to add to the cozy ambiance.   Stamped concrete deck wraps around to patio in the backyard opening to a wooded backyard gently sloping to lake, to watch the sunsets, and let the beauty of the maple and oak trees blow in the wind.  Stainless kitchen appliances with screen porch off kitchen for your morning coffee. Large 2 plus car garage for all of your lake toys and boats, 100 amp electrical.   Private lake and land 30 min to Duluth, close to Jay Cooke State Park and minutes to Carlton.   This is the property you have been waiting for, see it today!  Join us for lunch open house November 10 12:-1:00.

description: Recently sold: $275,000. House is located down a private lane and sits atop a hill overlooking a valley which people have described as looking like a beautiful national park. Just to complete the package you will enjoy peace with lots of hardwoods for hiking, biking, snow shoeing and so much more...

description: Recently sold: $210,000. This well maintained and move in ready home is nestled among the tall pines in the heart of Carlton.  Home features a very large living room with a wood burning fireplace, and built in cabinets.  There is an open floor plan with formal dining adjacent to the living room and updated spacious kitchen.   There are beautiful views of the wooded back yard from all the windows in the main living space.   The main floor has 3 bedrooms all with hardwood floors and large closets; the master boasting 2!   The bathroom has been updated with new flooring, tile surround in the bath, and a built in linen closet.  There is a sunroom off of the master bedroom with a door leading to the patio and back yard.   The basement is large, open, insulated, and is just waiting to be finished.  Home has fresh paint, new light fixtures, updated boiler, and water heater throughout. Outside there is a 2 car attached garage, 2nd garage with overhead door that could be used as a workshop or extra storage for boats, ATV, etc.  The 2nd garage also has a loft area that is finished with a deck and makes a great extra family space.  The yard is large and park like with a fire pit and lots of privacy and yard space to hang out and garden.  Home is waiting for the next buyer to enjoy!

description: Recently sold: $299,900. The best of both worlds - a turn key, horse ready farm along with the beauty of Chub Lake across the road.  The original home was built in the 1800's but the addition in 2013 more than doubled the size but still retained the charm and character of the entire property.  Rolling fields in the back have been completely re-fenced to be 11 fenced pastures.  Property comes with a historic 32x90 barn with hay loft, 34x80 pole building barn with 11 stalls, tack room, wash rack, lounge, 1/2 bath and feed room.  There is also a 60x90 indoor riding arena.  The home has been completely re-done with new bathrooms, furnace, electric service and septic system when the large addition was done.  Sit and enjoy the view of Chub Lake on the open deck or under the covered porch.  Great location that's less than a half hour to downtown Duluth and so close to the small town feel of downtown Carlton - restaurants, the high school, Jay Cooke Park and the Munger Trail.

description: Recently sold: $275,900. Enjoy the peacefulness and functionality of this updated 6+ bedroom, 3,000 sq. ft. ranch style home, sitting on 5 acres. description: Recently sold: $665,000. Private 2.33 acre site on Chub Lake with over 200ft of shoreline. Situated on dead end of the blacktopped road you will find this one owner, loved, 3BD/3BA home. The home is heated and cooled by GEO-thermal in ground heat pump system w/4000ft of buried piping. The main floor is 2 zone in floor, or turn off to use the force air side which heats and cools the upstairs too. Plenty of Storage in the 40x40 Morton building with 2-10ft overhead doors & 1-13.5 overhead with opener, and a 26-28 detached garage with 2 overhead doors/openers. All buildings have steel siding and roofs; concrete and blacktop drive and parking. The main yard is fully irrigated w/5zone in ground sprinkler. 2-concrete stamped patios, one is covered which enters the kitchen w/hickory cabinets & 6-11 walk-in pantry. Hickory builtins in the office off of kitchen and gas fireplace in the livingroom. The master suite has a 4pc granite bath, 2 walkin closets w/Ikea organizers. Plus 2BD & 1fullBA up. Main Fl laundry & bath

description: Recently sold: $575,000. Welcome to 75 Parkview Lane.  This home will have the all of your needs checked off.  Home features 10 acres, 3 bedrooms, 3 baths, open floor plans on all levels for entertaining guests, garages (2 are heated) to hold all of your vehicles/toys, with one of the garages set up for a mother-in-law or guest suite.  As soon as you walk into this home you will notice the Great Room that overlooks the park-like backyard and the wood burning fireplace that has a rock surround with a wood mantle. The main level features a kitchen that is complete with Heartland high-end appliances, a dining room with views for miles and access to the spacious deck. To finish off the main level is the Master Bedroom with a walk-in closet. The Lower Level features a family room with another wood-burning fireplace and opens up to the billiards room with a beautiful tin ceiling. Can step out the lower level to a covered patio, firepit, manicured backyard and even enjoy the 10x20 sauna.  The top level of this home will have 2 spacious bedrooms, a bathroom and an area in the hallway to set-up for studying or just relaxing.  This home is within 20 minutes of Duluth, trails to access Jay Cooke State Park just outside of the property lines and room to house horses.  This home truly has it all.
